 stand’. However, the tradition is very confused. The name was introduced in this form to Britain by the Normans, among whom it was popular as a result of the fame of  St Eustace , a Norman nobleman who was said to have been converted to Christianity by the vision of a crucifix between the antlers of the stag he was hunting."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":33,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":42,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":77,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Eustace LeGrosse was born about 1182, in Linton, Herefordshire, England. He had at least 2 daughters."},"et":{"about 1182–":"umbes 1182–Surnud","1202–Female":"1202–Surnud","1222–1257":"1222–1257","1182–Male":"1182–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1182":"umbes 1182","1224":"1224","1257":"1257","1202":"1202","1222":"1222","1182":"1182","Linton, Herefordshire, England":"Linton, Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1182–":"noin 118